After months of problems and uncertainty, the Africa Cup of Nations (AFCON) kicks off on Sunday, January 09, when host nation Cameroon play Burkina Faso. World's leading broadcasters are ready to broadcast the month-long tournament across the globe. Cameroon - Indomitable Lions who have been preparing since the end of December are hoping to win their sixth AFCON title at home. The tournament was delayed by a year due to the novel coronavirus pandemic.